# Code owners.
#
# GitHub uses this file together with branch-protection rules
# (Settings → Branches → main → Require review from Code Owners)
# to ensure every PR touching the listed paths is reviewed by an
# explicit maintainer before merging.
#
# Add more handles or org/teams as the project grows. Everyone listed
# here is auto-requested as a reviewer on matching PRs; branch
# protection's "Require review from Code Owners" then makes their
# approval mandatory before merge.
#
# Syntax: <pattern>  <owner1> <owner2> ...
# See https://docs.github.com/articles/about-code-owners

# Default owner for everything in the repo.
*                       @skarl

# Tighter ownership on the things that affect speakers in the field —
# the deploy / install paths and the resolver code itself. Add
# additional reviewers here as the project grows.
/resolver/              @skarl
